WHO   — GAME THEORY — a polemos sphere
WHAT  — When your best move depends on what the other player does — and theirs on you — you've left simple decision-making and entered a game. Game theory is the mathematics of that bind: rivals, allies, bluffs, and threats reduced to payoffs and equilibria. It explains why two rational players can both choose to lose, and how cooperation can survive in a world built to punish it.
WHERE — a sphere of the field of conflict  Framework inputs: value; exchange; rivalry; the open question  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — When your best move depends on what the other player does — and theirs on you — you've left simple decision-making and entered a game. Game theory is the mathematics of that bind: rivals, allies, bluffs, and threats reduced to payoffs and equilibria. It explains why two rational players can both choose to lose, and how cooperation can survive in a world built to punish it.
